Package com.peyrona.mingle.lang.interfaces

Interface IXprEval

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    NAXE
    public interface IXprEval
    This interface represents an expression evaluator with the minimum needed requirements.

    Different CIL implementations could include their own expression evaluator with more functionality.

    Author:
    Francisco Jos√© Morero Peyrona Official web site at: https://github.com/peyrona/mingle

    • Method Detail

      • build

        IXprEval build​(java.lang.String infixXpr)
        throws MingleException
        Set the expression to be evaluated.

        This is equivalent to build( String infixExpr, null, null )
        In this case the expression evaluator will behave as traditional ones: it will evaluate the expression and will immediately return the result. No groups can be involved, neither futures (AFTER or WITHIN).
        It is IXprEval responsibility to check if expression has errors.

        Parameters:
        infixXpr - An infix Une valid expression to be evaluated.
        Returns:
        Itself.
        Throws:
        MingleException - If expression is empty. For any other error, it is returned by ::getErrors().

      • build

        IXprEval build​(java.lang.String infiXxpr,
               java.util.function.Consumer<java.lang.Object> onSolved,
               java.util.function.Function<java.lang.String,​java.lang.String[]> fnGroupWise)
        throws MingleException
        Set the expression to be evaluated.

        The Consumer parameter is mandatory for expressions containing AFTER and/or WITHIN clauses.
        Because these type of expressions can not be evaluated immediately, the Consumer will be invoked as soon as the result of the evaluation produces a result, and only then: only Une Basic Data Types (Boolean, Number and String) can be passed to the Consumer (never pass null).
        For "normal" expressions (those that do not include AFTER and/or WITHIN), this parameter is optional.
        If expression does not include 'ANY', neither 'ALL' directives, the fnGroupWise parameter is not needed and can be passed as NULL.
        It is IXprEval responsibility to check if expression has errors.

        Parameters:
        infiXxpr - An infix Une valid expression to be evaluated.
        onSolved - Invoked after the expression is fully evaluated, receiving the result. Can be null.
        fnGroupWise - An instance that complies with IRuntime interface. Needed only if the expression uses ALL or ANY.
        Returns:
        Itself.
        Throws:
        MingleException - If expression is empty. For any other error, it is returned by ::getErrors().

      • eval

        java.lang.Object eval()
        Evaluates the expression, which only occurs if all variables involved in the expression has already a value and ::getErrors() returns an empty Map.

        Returns:
        The result returned by the expression or null if:
        • The expression has errors (this can be checked using ::getErrors())
        • The expression is not ready to be evaluated: one or more variables are not yet initialized
        • The expression include AFTER or WITHIN: in these cases onSolved will be invoked at due time.
        See Also:
        #set(java.lang.String, java.util.function.Consumer), getErrors()

      • eval

        java.lang.Object eval​(java.lang.String varName,
                      java.lang.Object varValue)
        Adds a variable name with its value or updates the value if the variable already existed and invokes ::eval().

        It is IXprEval responsibility to check if expression has errors prior to its evaluation.
        Parameters:
        varName -
        varValue -
        Returns:
        The result of evaluating the expression or null if:
        • The expression has errors (this can be checked using ::getErrors())
        • The expression is not ready to be evaluated: one or more variables are not yet initialized
        • The expression is not affected by passed variable (the variable is not part of the expression)
        • The expression include AFTER or WITHIN: in these cases onSolved will be invoked at due time.
        See Also:
        eval()
